# Implementation Plan: Alpha YouTube Forge (V1.0)

This plan outlines the integration of a functional video production pipeline into the Alpha Browser dashboard, allowing CEO Luna to manage content creation from script to upload.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component: Production Module]

#### [NEW] [production/page.tsx](file:///C:/Users/smile/alpha-browser/src/app/production/page.tsx)
Create a new page to manage the YouTube production workflow.
- **Workflow Stepper:** Track progress (Scripting -> Asset Gen -> Rendering -> Upload).
- **Agent Integration:** Direct buttons to trigger the Researcher (for trends) and Designer (for visuals).
- **Local Forge Controller:** A UI to trigger local rendering scripts.

#### [MODIFY] [layout.tsx](file:///C:/Users/smile/alpha-browser/src/app/layout.tsx)
Add the "Production Forge" menu item to the sidebar under the "Operations" section.

#### [NEW] [scripts/render_video.py](file:///C:/Users/smile/alpha-browser/scripts/render_video.py) (Scratch Script)
A helper Python script to be used locally for assembling images, TTS, and text into a video file.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Navigate to `/production` and verify the UI renders.
- Verify the sidebar link works.

### Manual Verification
- Trigger a mock "Script Generation" using the dashboard UI.
- Verify that assets generated by the Designer appear in the production queue.
